{
  "texts": [
    "While effective at detection, it requires extensive computation and cannot directly remove backdoors.Fine-Pruning [3] identifies and removes neurons most activated by poisoned samples.",
    "However, this approach may damage model accuracy and cannot guarantee complete backdoor removal if the backdoor is distributed across multiple neurons.Neural Attention Distillation (NAD) [4] uses knowledge distillation to transfer attention from backdoored to clean models.",
    "NAD achieves strong results (clean accuracy ∼90%, ASR ∼7.2%) on CIFAR-10 with ResNet-18, representing current state-of-the-art for backdoor unlearning.",
    "However, NAD requires a clean teacher model and provides no interpretable feedback during the unlearning process.",
    "Machine UnlearningMachine unlearning [6] aims to selectively remove specific training samples' influence from a trained model without full retraining.Gradient Ascent Methods maximize loss on backdoor samples to reverse their learned influence."
  ]
}